&#39;qqiztasining ittifoqidir.&nbsp;Bu a&#39;zolik ko&#39;plab muhandislik maktablari o&#39;rtasida talabalar almashish imkonini beradi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jahon universitetlari reytingi:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>QS World University reytingi #39</li>\r\n	<li>Times Higher Education World University Rankings*</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yana nima:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Xalqaro</strong>&nbsp;sertifikat</li>\r\n	<li>3 AKTS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','<p><strong>Training Dates</strong><br />\r\n11 Jan 2021 &ndash; 22 Jan 2021<br />\r\n<strong>Place&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nOnline Zoom Master Classes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Features&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Space system engineers follow, and often lead, space projects from conception to delivery, working with other disciplines to define user needs, define requirements, and shape the final design before supporting the project through the assembly, integration, and testing phase and finally into operation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Join our International online School 2021!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Space Systems and Communications Engineering</em></strong>&nbsp;is a crucial discipline within the space sector, and a keen understanding of what it is and how it is applied is key in defining the success of any space mission, from a student-built CubeSat to a commercial communications satellite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To help prepare the next generation of Space Systems engineers, TU Berlin &amp; COURSENTO in collaboration with EU partner universities are inviting you to participate in the&nbsp;<strong>International online School 2021 &ldquo;<em>Innovation Technologies in Space Systems and Communications Engineering&rdquo;</em></strong>, to be held from 11 to 22 January 2021 via Zoom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The online Master Classes ensure the improvement of skills in the field of space systems as well as introduce the background and challenges of communications engineering. The course will also give students valuable insight into system engineering products and some real-world problems faced by space system engineers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>About SPACECOM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong><em>&ldquo;New Study Program in Space Systems and Communications Engineering&rdquo;</em></strong><strong>&nbsp;&ndash; SPACE.COM</strong>&nbsp;is a three-year duration multi-country joint project co-funded by the Erasmus+ Capacity Building in the Field of Higher Education Programme of the European Union (EU) launched in 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<strong><em>aim</em></strong>&nbsp;of the project is to support the development, implementation, and accreditation of the new practice-oriented, student-focused MA program &ldquo;SPACE.COM&rdquo; to ensure the sustainability of Uzbekistan space systems engineering.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The project will create an innovative teaching and learning environment for the education of highly skilled specialists in line with the labor market and according to EU best practices and the Bologna process. The innovative character of the project will ensure the improvement of engineers&rsquo; soft skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The SPACE.COM project will also increase industrial cooperation between EU and UZ HEIs and other organizations interested in partnership, including cooperation in the field of space.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Agenda</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>11 Jan 2021 &ndash; 14 Jan 2021</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Mo.<br />\r\n			11.01.2021</strong></td>\r\n			<td>Venue: Online Zoom Master Class</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>9 AM &ndash; 10 AM (CET