p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Special subject</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">Mandatory</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:16px; width:170px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Language</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">Uzbek/Russian</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:16px; width:283px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Weekly lesson plan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"2\" style=\"height:28px; width:57px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>1.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:28px; width:151px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Name of subject</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:95px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Classroom hours</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:113px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Self-contained</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>hours</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:169px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Total number of hours</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:17px; width:151px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">Certification of measuring instruments in the field of aeronautical and space technology</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:17px; width:95px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">30</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:17px; width:113px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">30</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:17px; width:169px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">60</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:586px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:4px; width:57px\">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>2</strong><strong>.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:4px; width:529px\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\"><strong>Aims and objectives of the discipline</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">The purpose of this discipline is to study the mastery of test methods, operation, standardization and certification of aeronautical objects.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">Objectives:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">- Study of the basic concepts, procedures and participants in compulsory and voluntary product certification in Uzbekistan and abroad;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">- Study of the regulatory framework for certification in the Republic of Uzbekistan and the Eurasian Economic Union;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">- Study of the basic concepts, procedures and participants in the certification of civil aeronautical equipment;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">- Study of the Aviation Regulations governing the certification procedure and airworthiness standards for various categories of aircraft;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:1.0pt\">- To develop skills in completing the working documentation for the certification process.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>2.2 The main part</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>1- Module: </strong><strong>Aims and purposes of product testing </strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>1- Topic: Basic concepts in certification</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pedagogical techniques used in the module: </strong>case study method, pair work with partners, using presentations to consolidate the information that &nbsp;received.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>2- Topic: </strong>Legal framework for national certification</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>The</strong> <strong>pedagogical techniques used in the module include: </strong>writing out basic terms, working in pairs, using presentations to strengthen the information obtained.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>3- Topic: Fundamentals of aircraft for test technology</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>The</strong> <strong>pedagogical techniques used in the module include: </strong>writing out basic terms, working in pairs, using presentations to strengthen the information learned.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>4- Topic: Quality certification of aeronautical equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>The pedagogical techniques used in the module include: </strong>writing out basic terms, working in pairs, using presentations to strengthen the information learned.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5- Topic: Attestation of component parts</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pedagogical techniques used in the module: </strong>case study method, working in pairs, use of presentations to strengthen the information learned.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6- Topic: Features of flight tests</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pedagogical techniques used in the module: </strong>case study method, paired work, use of presentations to strengthen the information learned.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>7- Topic: Improving the effectiveness of testing in the certification of aeronautical equipment.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>Pedagogical techniques used in the module: </strong>case study method, working in pairs, use of presentations to strengthen the information learned.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\"><strong>2.3 Practical work on the subject</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1. Terminology, certification rules and procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2. Complex technical systems (CTS) and their characteristics</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>certification.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3. Activities of organizations in the field of certification of aeronautical equipment.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">&nbsp;4. Airworthiness standards.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5. Foreign practice of airworthiness standards.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6. Types of airworthiness certificate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7. General principles of certification work.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8. Development of a certification scheme for a passenger aircraft.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\">Practical work on the course is conducted once a week and takes one academic hour in a classroom where students and the instructor are present. Students are provided with slides, printed information resources related to the occupational &nbsp;works, as well as a quiz at the end of the course and an end assignment to widen the material resources.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:-.05pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:7.8pt\"><strong>2.4 </strong><strong>Independent work on the </strong><strong>topic</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:7.8pt\">Topics for independent work:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">1. Forms of product quality assurance</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">2. terms and definitions. Basic certification procedures</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">3. global certification practices. Activities of international organizations in the field of certification</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">4. Complex technical systems and features of their certification.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">5. International Civil Aviation Organization ICAO.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">6. Aviation Regulations AP-23, AP-25, AP-21, AP-29</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:14.15pt\">7. Attestation and certification of component parts</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; Independent work by undergraduate students to be submitted in the form of presentations or essays</p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:7.8pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:46px; width:56px\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>3.</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:46px; width:530px\">\r\n			<p><a name=\"_Hlk41903147\"><strong>Students&#39; knowledge and competence</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:7.8pt\">Knowledge gained after mastering the Master&#39;s subject:</p>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Study of the basic concepts, procedures and participants in compulsory and voluntary product certification in Uzbekistan and abroad;</li>\r\n				<li>Study of the regulatory framework for certification in the Republic of Uzbekistan and the Eurasian Economic Union;</li>\r\n				<li>Study of the basic concepts, procedures and participants in the certification of civil aeronautical equipment;</li>\r\n				<li>Study of the Aviation Regulations governing the certification procedure and airworthiness standards for various categories of aircraft;</li>\r\n				<li>Developing skills in completing work documentation</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:41.3pt\">when carrying out certification.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:24px; width:56px\">\r\n			<p style=\"te